Commentary Text: Rashid Khan to Stoinis, out Bowled! The straightener has done him in! Top of off-stump! A sigh of relief, after luck, D-Day panic, and every other factor going against them. Angling in towards middle, breaking just a little bit to straighten towards off-stump, and the overspin beats the trusting Stoinis as he is hastily pushed onto the backfoot to work this into the on-side - and it whizzes past the outside edge and takes the top of off-stump. Exhale, Sunrisers, the sun isn't going down yet... Stoinis b Rashid Khan 38(27) [4s-5 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Stoinis to Williamson, out Caught by Rabada!! Stoinis with the big wicket again. Everything he touches turns to gold, never mind the quality of delivery. This is a full, wide delivery. The idea is to go for the yorker but he has missed his mark by quite a bit. And precisely because he has, Williamson is able to lift it in the air and hit it straight down Rabada's throat at sweeper cover. Is this where Delhi book their ticket to the final?
